repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:54:3. Calls `InvalidateMeasure()` on each root, scheduling a full re-layout on the next frame.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:158:If your custom view (implemented via `ViewImpl`) caches pixel-unit values, those caches must be invalidated when scale changes. Since `InvalidateMeasure()` is called automatically on the root when `SetScale()` fires, derived views that override `OnMeasure` / `OnArrange` receive fresh constraints and `effectiveScale` on each layout pass — no extra work is required.
